Definition: a well-substantiated explanation of some aspect of the natural world
Example: an organized system of accepted knowledge that applies in a variety of circumstances to explain a specific set of phenomena; theories can incorporate facts and laws and tested hypotheses; true in fact and theory
Synonyms: noun, person, theorist, adj, all, theoretic, theoretician, explanation, a, well-substantiated, of, some, aspect, the, natural, world, an, organized, system, accepted, knowledge, that, applies, in, variety, circumstances, to, explain, specific, set, phenomena, theories, can, incorporate, facts, and, laws, tested, hypotheses, true, fact
Category: noun.cognition
